overview_description.description:
Banza is a food manufacturer that focuses on producing pasta products. Its first products feature a pasta made from chickpeas.

The company is driven by a mission to make nutritious food more accessible. Its products are now available in 8,000 stores, including Target, Kroger, and Whole Foods. Banza has been endorsed in the NYT, Food & Wine, Bon Appetit, on Good Morning America, Today, and been named one of TIME Magainze's 25 Best Inventions of the Year.

Banza was founded in 2014 and is headquartered in Detroit, Michigan.
